<subSubSection id="48D355CA8ED0FF5E48A755A2FE0CFB4D" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418ED0FF5E48A755A2FEB2FD56" blockId="158.[151,1436,151,2034]" box="[151,279,654,678]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48ED0FF5E489055A2FEA8FD56" box="[160,269,654,678]" captionStart="PLATE 41" captionStartId="159.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[261,1330,223,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-94@159.[241,1345,193,1856]" captionText="PLATE 41. A, C, E. Chelae. B, D. Male genitalia. A. Anteon punctum, holotype (from He &amp; Xu, 2002). B. A. qinlingense, holotype (from He &amp; Xu, 2002). C. A. quatei from Malaya (from Olmi 1998e). D. Anteon quatei, paratype (from Olmi 1991). E. A. raptor, holotype (from Olmi 1998e). Scale bar 0.26 mm for A, 0.23 mm for B, 0.13 mm for C, 0.17 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278512" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278512/files/figure.png" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Plate 41B</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418ED0FF5E48A755FBFD57FD1C" blockId="158.[151,1436,151,2034]" box="[151,754,726,749]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Anteon qinlingense He &amp; Xu 2002: 208; Xu et al. 2012a: 8.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418ED0FF5E48A75435FC43FB69" blockId="158.[151,1436,151,2034]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">
Description of Male. Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48ED0FF5E4A965435FCA6FCC1" box="[678,771,793,817]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="158" pageNumber="159" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
. Head black; antenna black-brown, except segments 5–6 brown and 7–10 testaceous; mesosoma and metasoma black; forelegs and midlegs testaceous; hindlegs brown, except trochanter testaceous. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 16:9:10:10:10:10:10:10:10:16. Head shiny; face with anterior half granulated and posterior half strongly punctate; POL = 9; OL = 5.5; OOL = 8.5; OPL = 3; TL = 4.5; greatest breadth of posterior ocelli shorter than POL (3.5:9); occipital carina complete; frontal line complete. Scutum, scutellum and metanotum shiny, punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Notauli incomplete, reaching approximately 0.5 length of scutum. Propodeum reticulate rugose, with strong transverse keel between dorsal and posterior surface; posterior surface with two longitudinal keels, median area smooth and shiny and lateral areas reticulate rugose. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; distal part of stigmal vein much shorter than proximal part (4:7). Paramere (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48ED0FF5E4C6D5371FB68FB85" box="[1117,1229,1117,1141]" captionStart="PLATE 41" captionStartId="159.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[261,1330,223,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-94@159.[241,1345,193,1856]" captionText="PLATE 41. A, C, E. Chelae. B, D. Male genitalia. A. Anteon punctum, holotype (from He &amp; Xu, 2002). B. A. qinlingense, holotype (from He &amp; Xu, 2002). C. A. quatei from Malaya (from Olmi 1998e). D. Anteon quatei, paratype (from Olmi 1991). E. A. raptor, holotype (from Olmi 1998e). Scale bar 0.26 mm for A, 0.23 mm for B, 0.13 mm for C, 0.17 mm for D, 0.26 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278512" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278512/files/figure.png" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Plate 41B</figureCitation>
) with distal inner pointed process and with proximal membranous process. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418ED0FF5E48F75389FE0CFB4D" blockId="158.[151,1436,151,2034]" box="[199,425,1189,1213]" pageId="158" pageNumber="159">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
